        <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
            <head>Biographical/Historical Information </head>
            <p>Edward Payson (1783-1827), an American Congregational preacher, was born on 25 July
                1783 in Rindge, New Hampshire, where his father, Seth Payson (1758-1820), was pastor
                of the Congregational Church. Edward Payson graduated from Harvard in 1803, and
                subsequently became principal of a school in Portland, Maine. In 1807 Payson became
                junior pastor of the Congregational Church of Portland. After becoming senior paster
                in 1811, Payson remained at the church until his death on 22
                October 1827. </p>
        </bioghist>
